HEADWORD: Sodamide
<hw>Sod*am"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A greenish or reddish crystalline substance,
<chform>NaNH2</chform>, obtained by passing ammonia over heated
sodium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

